00:00:03,190 --> 00:00:10,550

3
00:00:15,410 --> 00:00:16,810

4
00:00:24,530 --> 00:00:26,110
The other day, the Hospital Director

5
00:00:26,110 --> 00:00:30,280
asked me to be the head of the Clinic.

6
00:00:31,430 --> 00:00:34,160
I told her that I would think about it.

7
00:00:34,170 --> 00:00:38,150
You don't intend to refuse, do you?

8
00:00:39,170 --> 00:00:41,230
I do intend to refuse.

9
00:00:41,230 --> 00:00:43,070
Why?

10
00:00:43,560 --> 00:00:46,290
I thought it over for a long time

11
00:00:46,290 --> 00:00:51,420
An old man like me shouldn't be the head of the Clinic.

12
00:00:52,990 --> 00:00:56,160
Lee Si Joon, you should do it.

13
00:00:57,790 --> 00:01:02,260
That makes no sense. How can I be the Clinic head?

14
00:01:02,260 --> 00:01:05,370
I can't do it. I won't do it. I don't want to.

15
00:01:05,370 --> 00:01:09,590
Don't just say you don't want to do it. Consider it sincerely.

16
00:01:09,590 --> 00:01:13,620
Think about what the right choice is for the patients.

17
00:01:15,590 --> 00:01:19,430
To treat this world that is going increasingly crazy

18
00:01:19,430 --> 00:01:24,630
we need treatment methods that are more varied than traditional methods.

19
00:01:24,630 --> 00:01:27,150
In order to do that, more advanced,

20
00:01:27,150 --> 00:01:30,010
multidisciplinary research is necessary, don't you think?

21
00:01:31,650 --> 00:01:34,620
And isn't that your dream?

22
00:01:35,570 --> 00:01:38,470
Oh, but still, I can't.

23
00:01:38,470 --> 00:01:41,020
You can think about it.

24
00:01:48,790 --> 00:01:52,490
I'd like to make another suggestion.

25
00:01:52,490 --> 00:01:58,060
Didn't you say this, Director? This nation has many wounds, but not enough cures.

26
00:01:58,060 --> 00:02:01,190
And that is why you thought of a Mental Health Clinic.

27
00:02:01,220 --> 00:02:04,350
Dr. Lee, more than anyone else, will operate

28
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:07,060
the mental health center towards that purpose.

29
00:02:07,060 --> 00:02:10,880
To be honest, I am quite flustered.

30
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:15,540
You know it yourself that Doctor Lee is like no other.

31
00:02:15,540 --> 00:02:18,380
That is precisely the reason for my hesitation.

32
00:02:18,380 --> 00:02:23,600
But it seems to me that you've always made choices that was different from others.

33
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:24,610
Me?

34
00:02:24,610 --> 00:02:27,630
Having studied medicine despite your family's opposition.

35
00:02:27,630 --> 00:02:32,640
And your choice to get into management in order to create a good hospital.

36
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:35,960
They were all brave choices.

37
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:38,820
I am sure that you've made those choices

38
00:02:38,820 --> 00:02:40,140
after thinking it over a lot.

39
00:02:40,140 --> 00:02:42,380
And Dr. Lee, just because his personality is eccentric,

40
00:02:42,380 --> 00:02:44,880
he does not treat the patients in an eccentric way.

41
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:47,230
The treatment methods Dr. Lee is using now

42
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:51,300
are the results of having studied day and night for a very long time.

43
00:03:07,030 --> 00:03:09,280
Dr. Lee, since he was a resident, until now,

44
00:03:09,310 --> 00:03:11,900
he never stopped his research.

45
00:03:12,590 --> 00:03:15,750
When he was a resident he practically

46
00:03:15,750 --> 00:03:19,990
lived with his patients in the hospital ward.

47
00:03:19,990 --> 00:03:25,570
I've never met another doctor who only thinks about his patients whenever he is awake like Dr. Lee does.

48
00:03:27,460 --> 00:03:32,570
I acknowledge that Dr. Lee's treatment methods are excellent.

49
00:03:32,570 --> 00:03:36,630
The healing of the patient is the main purpose of the mental health clinic.

50
00:03:36,630 --> 00:03:39,320
Isn't that what you said, Director?

51
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:41,510
If so, then what is the problem?

52
00:03:41,510 --> 00:03:44,650
Whatever method is used, how is that important?

53
00:03:46,790 --> 00:03:51,590
Director, the mental health clinic should be entrusted, not to someone like Vice President Oh

54
00:03:51,590 --> 00:03:55,270
but a young person who is not afraid of change or experimentation.

55
00:03:55,270 --> 00:03:58,990
Please try entrusting him. I will diligently

56
00:03:58,990 --> 00:04:01,390
stay by his side to help him.

57
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:36,250
Ah, yes, Director.

58
00:04:38,990 --> 00:04:41,760
Oh, you're working so hard.

59
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:56,990
Welcome.

60
00:04:56,990 --> 00:04:59,350
My office felt stuffy

61
00:04:59,350 --> 00:05:01,180
so I asked to meet you here.

62
00:05:01,180 --> 00:05:03,560
And the weather is so nice today.

63
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:05,210
Yes.

64
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:07,530
Please sit.

65
00:05:09,470 --> 00:05:11,640
The preparations for the mental health clinic is going well?

66
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:15,770
Of course. I'm putting so much effort into it.

67
00:05:15,770 --> 00:05:20,630
All you've left to do is make that decision you've been putting off.

68
00:05:20,630 --> 00:05:24,610
So, about that,

69
00:05:24,610 --> 00:05:27,900
I just made an important decision.

70
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:30,730
I hope that you won't oppose it, Vice President.

71
00:05:30,730 --> 00:05:33,560
Have I ever disagreed with your decisions, Director?

72
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:34,830
I always respected them.

73
00:05:34,830 --> 00:05:38,520
That is true, but I think you will disagree this time.

74
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:40,510
How can that be?

75
00:05:40,510 --> 00:05:42,600
That will never happen.

76
00:05:43,370 --> 00:05:48,760
So our first head of the Mental Health Clinic

77
00:05:49,430 --> 00:05:52,570
will be Dr. Lee Si Joon.
 - What?

78
00:05:52,570 --> 00:05:55,040
Dr. Lee Si Joon.

79
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:57,650
That was unexpected, wasn't it?

80
00:05:58,350 --> 00:05:59,460
Are you that shocked?

81
00:05:59,460 --> 00:06:02,940
- Director, this isn't right.
 - What?

82
00:06:02,940 --> 00:06:05,040
Not even Park Dae Ha, but Lee Si Joon?

83
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:07,030
You're going to make Lee Si Joon the head of the clinic?

84
00:06:07,030 --> 00:06:09,250
Do you not know what kind of person he is?

85
00:06:09,250 --> 00:06:12,270
I do know, that is why I'm giving him this responsibility.

86
00:06:12,270 --> 00:06:14,150
This is Park Dae Ha's scheme, huh?

87
00:06:14,150 --> 00:06:15,990
You should not do this, Director.

88
00:06:15,990 --> 00:06:17,630
I cannot accept this at all.

89
00:06:17,630 --> 00:06:19,220
How can you say Lee Si Joon is the head of the clinic?

90
00:06:19,220 --> 00:06:22,610
Vice President, you're crossing the line.

91
00:06:22,610 --> 00:06:24,970
It's because this is so ridiculous.

92
00:06:24,970 --> 00:06:28,660
That cannot happen. Lee Si Joon cannot be the head of the clinic.

93
00:06:33,510 --> 00:06:37,040
Of all the people in the world, Lee Si Joon? Is she joking?

94
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:46,580

95
00:06:51,910 --> 00:06:53,840

96
00:06:57,410 --> 00:06:59,940
No, that's what I heard.

97
00:06:59,950 --> 00:07:05,480
The Vice President was so upset and saying that Lee Si Joon cannot become the head of the clinic.

98
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:07,490
So he's not the head yet, right?

99
00:07:07,490 --> 00:07:10,760
No, he must have already become the head, and that is why Vice President opposes it.

100
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:12,260
Isn't that a great thing?

101
00:07:12,260 --> 00:07:13,560
It's quite a twist.

102
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:16,910
I thought the head would be the Vice President.

103
00:07:16,910 --> 00:07:19,220
Dr. Lee isn't answering his phone, though.

104
00:07:20,010 --> 00:07:22,390
He wouldn't say no to the offer, will he?

105
00:07:22,390 --> 00:07:25,170
I think that he will.

106
00:07:25,170 --> 00:07:28,310
Theatrical therapy has three main methods.

107
00:07:28,310 --> 00:07:31,490
The first is when the participant uses his body

108
00:07:31,490 --> 00:07:34,490
and the sense of touch to express himself.

109
00:07:34,490 --> 00:07:38,690
The second is to use objects

110
00:07:38,700 --> 00:07:40,950
to express himself.

111
00:07:40,950 --> 00:07:43,180
Today, we will use this cloth

112
00:07:43,180 --> 00:07:47,170
to express our emotions.

113
00:08:04,070 --> 00:08:06,810
What meaning does this have?

114
00:08:06,810 --> 00:08:09,270
These are stepping stones.

115
00:08:09,270 --> 00:08:13,820
So I am stepping on these stones to cross over.

116
00:08:14,450 --> 00:08:16,850
The floor is the water.

117
00:08:16,860 --> 00:08:23,880
And I am standing about here.

118
00:08:25,260 --> 00:08:27,360
But there is a strong wave in the water.

119
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:30,190
So I'm waiting for the wave to pass.

120
00:08:30,190 --> 00:08:34,660
And as I wait, I exercise like this.

121
00:08:34,660 --> 00:08:36,270
That is so good.

122
00:08:36,270 --> 00:08:39,640
Let's all give Woo Joo a round of applause.

123
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:48,360
What brings you here?

124
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:51,040
Can you make some time for me today?

125
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:52,180
Has something happened?

126
00:08:52,180 --> 00:08:57,800
I have something to ponder about, and I thought that being with you will help me find the answer.

127
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:59,830
Wow, I am someone who can give you answers?

128
00:08:59,830 --> 00:09:02,490
- You didn't know that?
 - I did not.

129
00:09:04,190 --> 00:09:07,500
Well, I am quite busy, but

130
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:09,380
I will spend time with you.

131
00:09:09,380 --> 00:09:13,030
What are you doing, anyway? How long will you hide it from me?

132
00:09:13,030 --> 00:09:15,280
- Maybe in about a year from now?
- Huh?

133
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:16,660
I will surprise you.

134
00:09:16,660 --> 00:09:18,520
A whole year?

135
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:21,910
Then we can do what I want today, right?

