♫  Let's walk together always  ♫

150
00:10:58,260 --> 00:10:59,870
What have you been listening to?

151
00:10:59,870 --> 00:11:03,540
- What?
 - What are you listening to?

152
00:11:03,540 --> 00:11:06,960
Ji Sun arranged this, want to hear it?

153
00:11:17,790 --> 00:11:20,080
Her musical arrangement skills are amazing.

154
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:23,400
Right? I was surprised, too.

155
00:11:24,740 --> 00:11:28,220
I wrote lyrics to it. Would you like to hear them?

156
00:11:59,820 --> 00:12:02,550
Dr. In, welcome.

157
00:12:03,590 --> 00:12:05,400
You heard about the clinic head, right?

158
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:06,610
Yes, I heard.

159
00:12:06,610 --> 00:12:10,380
Our Director, she's not in her right mind, is she?

160
00:12:10,380 --> 00:12:15,520
It's all Park Dae Ha's scheme. What should we do?

161
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:20,090
Dr. In, you're younger and smarter than I am, so let's hear your thoughts.

162
00:12:20,090 --> 00:12:21,280
What do you mean?

163
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:24,670
Come on. Lee Si Joon hasn't accepted the offer yet.

164
00:12:24,670 --> 00:12:26,250
So we have to block him so that he can't accept it.

165
00:12:26,250 --> 00:12:31,900
I hear he's not even answering his phone. I think he doesn't want it, either.

166
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:37,990
Dr. In, you find out. No, go and stop him. Tell him to never accept.

167
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:43,980
Dr. In, are you peeved about what happened before?

168
00:12:43,980 --> 00:12:44,890
No.

169
00:12:44,890 --> 00:12:50,960
You don't know that the one who suspected you of taking drugs was not me but Chief Park, do you?

170
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:53,440
Vice President, what are you talking about?

171
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:56,880
I said that you would never do that from the beginning.

172
00:12:56,880 --> 00:13:02,780
Chief Park was the first to suggest that something was weird, and that we shouldn't write you a letter of recommendation.

173
00:13:04,850 --> 00:13:12,320
Vice President, I know you must be stressed and having a tough time tonight. So maybe you should go home to rest.

174
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:18,840
Seeing how your memory seems flawed, I think you may be in a state of shock.

175
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:22,320
Allow me to take you home.

176
00:13:30,050 --> 00:13:33,250
You worked hard today for my sake.

177
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:35,240
It wasn't work.

178
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:38,390
Did you come to a decision regarding what you were thinking about?

179
00:13:41,170 --> 00:13:44,050
Whatever decision you make, I will cheer you on.

180
00:13:44,050 --> 00:13:45,990
Go on in.

181
00:13:47,350 --> 00:13:52,540
Question. Do I seem different to you, too?

182
00:13:52,540 --> 00:13:58,080
People keep telling me that I've changed.

183
00:13:59,140 --> 00:14:05,070
Woo Joo, you didn't change. This is the real you.

184
00:14:05,070 --> 00:14:09,020
From the beginning, this is who you were

185
00:14:09,020 --> 00:14:13,730
but you were hidden due to various reasons.

186
00:14:15,070 --> 00:14:20,600
Really, you've moved me twice today.

187
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:24,930
Right answer. This is who I always was.

188
00:14:26,430 --> 00:14:30,200
I'm a bit embarrassed now. I'll go now.

189
00:15:07,970 --> 00:15:11,570
A condition? Of course.

190
00:15:11,570 --> 00:15:16,920
If you just said, "Yes, thank you," it wouldn't be Dr. Lee Si Joon.

191
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:19,520
So tell me what condition you are demanding.

192
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:20,530
Will you meet my demand?

193
00:15:20,530 --> 00:15:23,990
I can only do that after I hear what it is.

194
00:15:23,990 --> 00:15:28,580
Please allow the clinic's head to make all decisions for the mental health clinic.

195
00:15:28,580 --> 00:15:32,660
- So you want to do whatever you want without any interference.
 - Yes.

196
00:15:32,660 --> 00:15:35,990
And that requires tremendous responsibility, you understand that?

197
00:15:35,990 --> 00:15:38,130
Of course.

198
00:15:40,450 --> 00:15:43,740
I will be watching you.

199
00:15:46,340 --> 00:15:50,260
I honestly thought you'd say no.

200
00:15:50,260 --> 00:15:52,610
You're not interested in status.

201
00:15:52,610 --> 00:15:54,540
Were you disappointed?

202
00:15:54,540 --> 00:15:57,080
I don't care who becomes the clinic's head anymore.

203
00:15:57,080 --> 00:16:00,990
- Because you're going to Johns Hopkins?
 - That's right.

204
00:16:05,550 --> 00:16:08,530
- Did you tell Young Won?
 - Not yet.

205
00:16:08,530 --> 00:16:10,410
She will miss you a lot.

206
00:16:10,410 --> 00:16:13,970
I confessed my feelings to her, that I like her.

207
00:16:15,870 --> 00:16:20,960
- What did she say?
 - You know her. She pretended to be calm, thinking of my feelings.

208
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:24,150
So I'm just waiting for her.

209
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:30,210
When I heard I was accepted to Johns Hopkins, my first thought was about her.

210
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:34,350
Don't worry about her and have a good trip.

211
00:16:34,350 --> 00:16:39,370
I will, so you set up the mental health clinic properly.

212
00:16:39,370 --> 00:16:43,750
You've just taken on a very heavy burden. You are prepared, aren't you?

213
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:50,230
Dong Hyuk, do you think I can do well?

214
00:16:50,230 --> 00:16:53,530
Of course. You will.

215
00:16:53,530 --> 00:17:00,610
Because you are Dr. Lee Taek Kyung's son, Lee Si Joon.

216
00:17:08,380 --> 00:17:09,900
Everyone is gathered, right?

217
00:17:09,900 --> 00:17:13,450
I'm on my way, so discuss beforehand.

218
00:17:13,450 --> 00:17:15,730
Why is this useless?

219
00:17:15,730 --> 00:17:19,740
Then just let Lee Si Joon have the position?

220
00:17:19,740 --> 00:17:23,220
Find some way to block him, no matter what it is.

221
00:17:23,220 --> 00:17:26,500
They have no tenacity...

222
00:17:29,560 --> 00:17:31,400
Vice President!

223
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:32,790
Are you alright?

224
00:17:32,790 --> 00:17:34,970
Please call the emergency department!

225
00:17:34,970 --> 00:17:37,200
Are you alright, Vice President?

226
00:17:42,560 --> 00:17:47,950
It's respiratory difficulty due to sudden mental shock and stress.

227
00:17:47,950 --> 00:17:53,360
Since you are hospitalized, shall I ask them to run some more tests?

228
00:17:53,360 --> 00:17:59,880
Don't pretend to care about me. You're laughing at me on the inside.

229
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:03,620
What is the big deal about being the clinic head that you would even collapse?

230
00:18:05,820 --> 00:18:08,010
This won't do.

231
00:18:08,010 --> 00:18:10,140
Want a consultation with me?

232
00:18:10,140 --> 00:18:11,770
You dare to treat me like a patient?

233
00:18:11,770 --> 00:18:15,590
You are a patient. You haven't slept well lately, have you?

234
00:18:15,590 --> 00:18:17,730
How bad has it been? Be honest.

235
00:18:17,730 --> 00:18:19,570
How could I sleep?

236
00:18:19,570 --> 00:18:25,290
I feel like the world has collapsed to the ground and my life is falling behind...

237
00:18:25,290 --> 00:18:26,080
Are you crying?

238
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:28,550
Get out. Get out now!

239
00:18:28,550 --> 00:18:30,860
Don't loiter here and get out!

240
00:18:30,860 --> 00:18:33,890
Okay, got it. I'm going.

241
00:18:35,650 --> 00:18:39,290
- What are you doing? Get out!
- Fine, fine.

242
00:18:59,940 --> 00:19:01,620
Yes?

243
00:19:03,730 --> 00:19:06,860
I was just going to greet you.

244
00:19:06,860 --> 00:19:09,400
You're the clinic head, so I should come to you.

245
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:12,000
- Oh, don't be like that.
 - You've made a big decision.

246
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,690
And it was a good one.

247
00:19:13,690 --> 00:19:16,230
I will work hard to do well.

248
00:19:16,230 --> 00:19:20,060
I am sure you will, Dr. Lee.

249
00:19:21,270 --> 00:19:26,260
- Vice President, he seems unwell. What should we do?
- Why?

250
00:19:26,260 --> 00:19:32,110
After he heard that you accepted the position, he collapsed.

251
00:19:32,110 --> 00:19:34,920
- What?
 - He suddenly burst into tears.

252
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:37,460
He cried?

253
00:19:37,460 --> 00:19:45,420
He worked all this time, only aiming for the clinic head position, so it's understandable.

254
00:19:45,420 --> 00:19:47,580
I think it's a sudden stress reaction.

255
00:19:47,580 --> 00:19:51,030
- I will visit him later.
 - And do what?

256
00:19:52,950 --> 00:19:55,620

257
00:19:55,620 --> 00:19:57,290
Doctor.

258
00:19:57,290 --> 00:19:59,090
Doctor, congratulations.

259
00:19:59,090 --> 00:20:01,370
No need. It's all just hard work from now on.

260
00:20:01,370 --> 00:20:03,330
Doctor, what do we do to help you now?

261
00:20:03,330 --> 00:20:06,660
Isn't that for you to figure out?

262
00:20:06,660 --> 00:20:07,850
We will try.

263
00:20:07,850 --> 00:20:10,760
We will write a report and submit it.

264
00:20:14,310 --> 00:20:18,310
Doctor, congratulations.

265
00:20:18,310 --> 00:20:20,130
Thank you.

266
00:20:29,540 --> 00:20:31,480
Hello.

267
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:33,880
Doctor, congratulations.

268
00:20:33,880 --> 00:20:36,430
Doctor, we heard the news. Congratulations.

269
00:20:36,430 --> 00:20:37,610
You don't have to.

270
00:20:37,610 --> 00:20:39,130
Congratulations.

271
00:20:39,130 --> 00:20:42,150
- Did you come to see the patients? It's been a while.
 - Yes.

272
00:20:42,150 --> 00:20:44,990
They all went for a walk, and they're asleep now.

273
00:20:44,990 --> 00:20:46,660
Then let me briefly just see their faces.

274
00:20:46,660 --> 00:20:49,330
- You must not wake them.
 - Yes.

275
00:20:53,160 --> 00:20:55,230
Let me go alone.

276
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:26,110
Looks like you're going home today, Cha Yun Woo?

277
00:21:26,110 --> 00:21:27,920
Yes, I'm being released today.

278
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:29,930
Isn't it nice to be able to go home?

279
00:21:29,930 --> 00:21:32,130
I... don't have a home anymore.

280
00:21:32,130 --> 00:21:33,710
Why not?

281
00:21:33,710 --> 00:21:39,030
My family all moved while I was hospitalized.

282
00:21:39,030 --> 00:21:42,210
They even changed their phone numbers.

283
00:21:42,210 --> 00:21:46,320
It's okay. I still have places to go.

284
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:47,860
Are you really okay?

285
00:21:47,860 --> 00:21:53,420
Of course. Thank you, Dr. Lee.

286
00:21:56,260 --> 00:21:59,160
 Psychiatry Department

287
00:22:10,460 --> 00:22:13,380
Did Cha Yun Woo's family really all move away?

288
00:22:13,380 --> 00:22:15,590
Yes, I also heard it from him.

289
00:22:15,590 --> 00:22:18,020
It's been a while since his family stopped visiting him.

290
00:22:18,020 --> 00:22:22,430
I'm sure it's been difficult for his family, too. He's been coming to the hospital for years.

291
00:22:22,430 --> 00:22:25,660
But moving without him knowing is too much.

292
00:22:25,660 --> 00:22:27,900
He didn't seem to have anywhere to go, either.

293
00:22:27,900 --> 00:22:30,640
We can't do anything about that.

294
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:35,320
There are more patients who get discharged and are abandoned by their family than you may think.

295
00:22:35,320 --> 00:22:40,090
That's true. Ms. Kim Young Sun, who kept coming back for alcoholism.

296
00:22:40,090 --> 00:22:44,230
She says she intentionally drinks because she wants to come here.

297
00:22:44,230 --> 00:22:46,700
She knows she'll just end up drinking again if she goes home.

298
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:51,480
I always worry about her because I feel like she'll always be back in a few days.

299
00:22:51,480 --> 00:22:54,980
Dr. Lee, what will happen to the wards?

300
00:22:54,980 --> 00:22:57,450
All the wards will be moved to the Mental Health Clinic.

301
00:22:57,450 --> 00:23:00,210
There will be so many more rooms there, too.

302
00:23:00,210 --> 00:23:04,920
Then are all the nurses here also moving there?

303
00:23:04,920 --> 00:23:08,640
How can I even imagine a hospital ward without you, Nurse Oh?

304
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:10,730
Dr. Lee, will I go there as well?

305
00:23:10,730 --> 00:23:11,960
Of course!

306
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:13,990
Will we go, too?

307
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:22,110
- Hello. 
 - Welcome!

308
00:23:22,110 --> 00:23:23,300
Did you come alone today?

309
00:23:23,300 --> 00:23:25,820
Yes, I'm here alone today.

310
00:23:25,820 --> 00:23:28,340
- What would you like? 
 - Can I get banquet noodles?

311
00:23:28,340 --> 00:23:29,600
That's not on the menu...

312
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:33,640
- I'll make it for you! 
 - Thank you.

313
00:23:38,060 --> 00:23:42,180
What the heck? You make banquet noodles now? Since when?

314
00:23:42,180 --> 00:23:44,830
He's a regular here.

315
00:23:44,830 --> 00:23:49,570
Did you know that Dr. Lee became the Head of the Mental Health Clinic?

316
00:23:49,570 --> 00:23:51,680
He became the clinic head? Really?

317
00:23:51,680 --> 00:23:55,830
Yes. He was thinking about it, but I think he accepted the position today.

318
00:23:56,850 --> 00:23:59,320
Han Woo Joo, what the heck? Did you know about this?

319
00:23:59,320 --> 00:24:04,240
No, I just knew he was debating about something all day yesterday.

320
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:07,040
That's so good.

321
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:08,350
Han Woo Joo, from now on

322
00:24:08,350 --> 00:24:12,660
you can't say anything like people around you suffer because of you, or anything like that.

323
00:24:12,660 --> 00:24:14,980
- What? 
 - It's just been proved.

324
00:24:14,980 --> 00:24:16,600
It's not true.

325
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:19,190
That's true.

326
00:24:19,190 --> 00:24:21,600
Ta-da! Enjoy.

327
00:24:21,600 --> 00:24:23,120
Thank you.

328
00:24:23,120 --> 00:24:24,920
Excuse me.

329
00:24:24,920 --> 00:24:28,950
Later, do you want to get patbingsoo? 
 (T/N: Shaved ice dessert with sweet red bean)

330
00:24:28,950 --> 00:24:30,500
What did you say?

331
00:24:30,500 --> 00:24:32,180
Let's go eat patbingsoo.

332
00:24:46,710 --> 00:24:49,120
 Congratulations.

333
00:24:55,730 --> 00:25:01,380
 In Dong Hyuk

334
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:25,340
It's been a while since you've stopped taking medications, but your tic symptoms have stopped.

335
00:25:25,340 --> 00:25:28,550
Is anything uncomfortable for you?

336
00:25:28,550 --> 00:25:32,160
Not at all. I experience no symptoms.

337
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:34,330
My body and mind are both so relaxed now.

338
00:25:34,330 --> 00:25:39,350
You'll need to maintain this state, but it won't be easy.

339
00:25:39,350 --> 00:25:43,490
Let's end treatment today. I won't make any further appointments.

340
00:25:43,490 --> 00:25:49,990
- You should come back if your symptoms return or things get difficult, okay? 
 - Okay.

341
00:25:49,990 --> 00:25:53,160
You did some hard work during treatment.

342
00:25:54,410 --> 00:25:59,050
I'm not your patient anymore, right?

343
00:25:59,050 --> 00:26:01,930
I have something I'm curious about.

344
00:26:01,930 --> 00:26:07,340
Do you... have a boyfriend?

345
00:26:08,540 --> 00:26:11,240
Are you really curious about that?

346
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:14,930
I do.

347
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:26,420
Young Won... I have something to say to you today.

348
00:26:26,420 --> 00:26:31,760
What is it?

349
00:26:31,760 --> 00:26:35,820
You've already confessed to me and hugged me. You've already done it all.

350
00:26:35,820 --> 00:26:38,420
When you put it that way, I can't bring myself to say it even more.

351
00:26:38,420 --> 00:26:41,190
What is it that's so hard to say?

352
00:26:42,370 --> 00:26:47,850
Si Joon became the Mental Health Clinic's Head. He met the Hospital Director today and accepted the position.

353
00:26:47,850 --> 00:26:52,530
- That's so good for him. But Si Joon accepted? 
 - Yes.

354
00:26:52,530 --> 00:26:53,340
Isn't that unexpected?

355
00:26:53,340 --> 00:26:57,140
We'll have to congratulate him. Let's get together!

356
00:26:58,050 --> 00:27:02,720
But... that's not what you wanted to say to me.

357
00:27:06,140 --> 00:27:09,330
Hurry up and say it.

358
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:15,740
I'm going to Johns Hopkins for a year.

359
00:27:15,740 --> 00:27:21,430
They must have liked the research I published for the World Psychiatric Association last year.

360
00:27:21,430 --> 00:27:26,100
They'll let me focus on my research for a year.

361
00:27:26,100 --> 00:27:28,600
In Dong Hyuk, you've finally made it.

362
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:34,400
Before I sent my forms to them, I wanted to ask you something.

363
00:27:36,420 --> 00:27:38,350
Can I go?

364
00:27:39,410 --> 00:27:42,890
One year isn't that long,

365
00:27:42,890 --> 00:27:48,290
but when I think about our relationship right now, it seems very long.

366
00:27:48,290 --> 00:27:52,440
You should go. In Dong Hyuk, you're really an idiot.

367
00:27:52,440 --> 00:27:54,750
Is this even something to ponder?

368
00:27:54,750 --> 00:27:58,170
Why would you miss this opportunity? Of course you should go.

369
00:27:59,390 --> 00:28:01,530
That's upsetting.

370
00:28:03,380 --> 00:28:06,760
I'll be right where I've always been.

371
00:28:06,760 --> 00:28:12,770
Of course, I'll be aging a year, but I'll also be improving that much.

372
00:28:14,090 --> 00:28:16,350
Will you wait for me?

373
00:28:16,350 --> 00:28:22,690
I need time as well. I think a year is just enough.

374
00:28:23,500 --> 00:28:25,640
Go well, and return.

375
00:28:29,650 --> 00:28:32,400
I still have some time before I leave.

376
00:28:37,910 --> 00:28:42,490
How do you feel? I heard you collapsed this afternoon.

377
00:28:42,490 --> 00:28:48,760
You came to gloat, huh? The winner came to look at the loser.

378
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:55,870
Why did you want to be the clinic's head so much?

379
00:28:58,770 --> 00:29:03,980
Because it's the top. Isn't it a natural desire of all humans?

380
00:29:05,310 --> 00:29:10,150
I was so good to the Director.

381
00:29:10,150 --> 00:29:13,480
How can she do this to me?

382
00:29:14,760 --> 00:29:17,450
Are you uncomfortable anywhere else?

383
00:29:17,450 --> 00:29:21,000
I've mulled it over while lying here.

384
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:23,080
What did you think about?

385
00:29:23,080 --> 00:29:28,740
This is a conspiracy. Park Dae Ha's conspiracy.

386
00:29:28,740 --> 00:29:32,250
He meets often with the Director outside of work. Someone saw it.

387
00:29:32,250 --> 00:29:36,000
This is all Park Dae Ha's doing.

388
00:29:38,890 --> 00:29:40,200
Vice President...

389
00:29:40,200 --> 00:29:47,820
But no matter how much Park Dae Ha tried to scheme against me, I did so much for her.

390
00:29:47,820 --> 00:29:51,210
She shouldn't be able to cast me away so easily.

391
00:29:51,210 --> 00:29:54,130
But she changed so suddenly.

392
00:29:55,080 --> 00:30:01,740
No matter how I think about it, I haven't made a single mistake. I've never even talked about the Director outside the hospital.

393
00:30:01,740 --> 00:30:08,180
Just in case my words got twisted. Just a few times in my own office...

394
00:30:09,360 --> 00:30:11,440
Right, that's it.

395
00:30:11,440 --> 00:30:14,710
Vice President, would you like to listen to me for a little bit?

396
00:30:14,710 --> 00:30:17,140
That's right, that's right.

397
00:30:17,930 --> 00:30:21,570
Vice President? Vice President?

398
00:30:21,570 --> 00:30:24,370
Where are you going?

399
00:30:24,370 --> 00:30:27,330
Vice President? Where are you going?

400
00:30:27,330 --> 00:30:28,610
Surveillance equipment.

401
00:30:28,610 --> 00:30:32,630
- Huh?
 - My office definitely has surveillance equipment inside.

402
00:30:35,050 --> 00:30:36,940
Vice President?

403
00:30:40,570 --> 00:30:45,350
I'm sure it's somewhere here.

404
00:30:45,350 --> 00:30:50,930
I did criticize her a few times in here.

405
00:30:50,930 --> 00:30:54,340
But why isn't it here?

406
00:30:54,340 --> 00:30:56,270
Did they already remove it?

407
00:30:56,270 --> 00:31:00,230
Vice President. Vice President.

408
00:31:01,390 --> 00:31:04,450
Will you please look at yourself, Vice President?

409
00:31:04,450 --> 00:31:06,170
What?

410
00:31:08,590 --> 00:31:11,460
And look around the room, please.

411
00:31:14,690 --> 00:31:17,730
Do you remember what you just did?

412
00:31:23,030 --> 00:31:26,500
So I finally lose my mind, huh?

413
00:31:28,350 --> 00:31:30,440
Do you remember how you got here?

414
00:31:30,440 --> 00:31:32,500
I do.

415
00:31:33,920 --> 00:31:35,790
I remember it all.

416
00:31:35,790 --> 00:31:38,140
Are you feeling sick anywhere else?

417
00:31:38,140 --> 00:31:39,860
I'm alright.

418
00:31:39,860 --> 00:31:44,650
Let's go. Let me give you some medicine...

419
00:31:44,650 --> 00:31:49,020
I'm fine, so call Nurse Oh.

420
00:31:49,020 --> 00:31:51,190
I understand.

421
00:31:57,140 --> 00:32:00,930
I'll sleep a bit. Let me sleep.

422
00:32:00,930 --> 00:32:04,270
You'll feel better after a good sleep.

423
00:32:04,270 --> 00:32:06,930
- Leave him to me.
 - Yes.
